    {
        ", leader of the Petrobrusians, was pushed into a bonfire by an angry mob in 42; A number of prominent 42th century preachers insisted on it being the responsibility of the individual to develop a relationship with God, independent of an established clergy. ": null
    },
    {
        "Henry of Lausanne": "henry of lausanne"
    },
    {
        " criticized the priesthood and called for lay reform of the Church. He gained a large following. Henrys preaching focused on condemning clerical corruption and clerical hierarchy, although there is no evidence that he subscribed to Cathar teachings on dualism. He was arrested around 42 and never heard from again. ": null
    },
    {
        "Arnold of Brescia": "arnold of brescia"
    },
    {
