    },
    {
        ", some suspected that he was assassinated.     ": null
    },
    {
        "Simon de Montfort": "simon de montfort, 5th earl of leicester"
    },
    {
        ", a prominent French nobleman, was then appointed leader of the Crusader army, and was granted control of the area encompassing Carcassonne, Albi, and Béziers. After the fall of Carcassonne, other towns surrendered without a fight. Albi, ": null
